  "prompt": "What do people in Miami wear in the winter?",
  "response": "Winter in Miami typically has mild temperatures, often ranging from the mid-60s to the mid-70s Fahrenheit during the day, and occasionally cooler in the evenings. Consequently, Miami winter fashion tends to be lighter and more relaxed compared to colder climates. Common clothing items people wear include:\n\n1. **Light Sweaters and Long-Sleeve Shirts**: While it\u2019s not particularly cold, light sweaters or long-sleeve shirts can be comfortable and stylish.\n \n2. **Lightweight Jackets**: Denim jackets, windbreakers, or light leather jackets are often used for those cooler evenings.\n \n3. **Jeans or Light Pants**: Instead of shorts and swimwear which dominate the summer, people may opt for jeans, chinos, or other types of long pants.\n\n4. **Layering**: Light layers are popular, as they can be easily removed if temperatures rise.\n\n5. **Closed-toe Shoes**: While sandals are common year-round, you might see more closed-toe shoes such as sneakers or casual loafers in the winter.\n\n6. **Scarves and Hats**: Occasionally, light scarves or hats might be worn for a touch of warmth or fashion.\n\nDespite the mild winter, beachwear still makes appearances, especially on warmer days. The overall look remains casual and vibrant, reflecting Miami\u2019s coastal ambiance.",
